ce:section.ce:para:
According to above analysis, we have designed a post-oxidation approach through a UV-assisted photochemical decomposition reaction with potassium persulfate (K2S2O8). K2S2O8 solution was used to produce sulfate radical anions (SO4
                     −

                     ) under UV light [23], which effectively conducted oxidative modification to obtain abundant carboxyl groups on the surface of GQDs. Besides, the oxidized GQDs’ detection capacity for Cu2+ was also studied. Since K2S2O8 only changed the oxidation degree on GQDs’ surface and the usage amount of that was small, the size and concentration of GQDs was unaltered and no other undesired heteroatoms were introduced in the process. Therefore, it is a green and mild method for surface modification of GQDs and the appliance for Cu2+ detection.
